pnpm/pnpm#10160.body:
## The Problem

During the **postinstall hoisting phase**, after a package is built, pnpm copies it to multiple hoisted locations using `hardLinkDir` (`exec/build-modules/src/index.ts:214`). When concurrent workers attempt to hard-link the same built package to overlapping destinations, an unhandled `ERR_PNPM_EEXIST` error occurs.


This is a **file system operation timing bug** in the postinstall hoisting process. When multiple workers simultaneously copy the same built package to shared hoisted locations, they race to create identical files. The error handling doesn't account for the timing window between directory creation and file linking.

### The Bug Location
https://github.com/pnpm/pnpm/blob/357490525a8ed2738732432f652a93ceed9a9c67/fs/hard-link-dir/src/index.ts#L58-L72
```typescript
function linkOrCopyFile (srcFile: string, destFile: string): void {
  try {
    linkOrCopy(srcFile, destFile) // 1st attempt
  } catch (err: unknown) {
    assert(util.types.isNativeError(err))
    if ('code' in err && err.code === 'ENOENT') {
      gfs.mkdirSync(path.dirname(destFile), { recursive: true })
      linkOrCopy(srcFile, destFile) // 2nd attempt - UNPROTECTED!
      return
    }
    if (!('code' in err && err.code === 'EEXIST')) {
      throw err
    }
  }
}
```

**The problem:** The 2nd `linkOrCopy` call is inside the catch block but not wrapped in try-catch. If it throws EEXIST, the error escapes uncaught.

### File System Operation Timeline

During postinstall hoisting, when Worker A and Worker B both try to copy the same built package to a shared hoisted location:

```
  T1: Worker A: 1st linkOrCopy -> ENOENT (parent dir missing in hoisted location)
  T2: Worker B: 1st linkOrCopy -> ENOENT (parent dir missing in hoisted location)
  T3: Worker A: mkdirSync(parent) -> creates directory
  T4: Worker B: mkdirSync(parent) -> no-op (dir exists, recursive: true)
  T5: Worker A: 2nd linkOrCopy -> success (file doesn't exist yet)
  T6: Worker B: 2nd linkOrCopy -> EEXIST (file created by Worker A) → UNCAUGHT!
```

The critical timing window is between T4 and T6 where both workers believe they can safely create the file in the hoisted location.

## Fix

Wrap the retry (line 23) in try-catch to handle concurrent EEXIST errors.


